anentrypoint-design mobile topbar jank root cause + fix (2026-05-28): the .app-topbar was a rigid 3-col grid (auto 1fr auto) but the Topbar component (shell.js) emitted an empty middle <span> when no search prop, so on mobile the 2-col @media grid (1fr auto) left nav in a 0px/overflow cell and its 9 nav links each collapsed to ~16px width, overlapping into unreadable text. FIX: switch .app-topbar to display:flex flex-wrap; emit null instead of an empty search span; give .app-topbar nav a {flex:0 0 auto} so links keep their width; at <=480/640px drop nav to its own full-width horizontally-scrollable row (flex:1 1 100%; max-width:none; order:3; overflow-x:auto). Also the crumb tagline Chip (site.tagline) wrapped to a ~127px-tall row on mobile - hide it <=640px (.app-crumb chip {display:none}), dropping chrome height 223px->146px. Fixed in app-shell.css + shell.js (v0.0.159) AND mirrored inline in gm site/theme.mjs <style> so the live gm site is correct on gh-pages deploy regardless of unpkg @latest timing. Pattern: critical responsive fixes go in BOTH the design package (all consumers) and the gm inline style (immediate live correctness). Diagnosed via live page as debugger: getBoundingClientRect on topbar children showed grid 350.4px 0px with 3 children and links at w:16.